               <orth>duine làn lagh</orth>
            </form>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-idp3253840">
            <form>
               <orth>duine amhrasach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>suspicious.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-idp3255352">
            <form>
               <orth>rag</orth>
            </form>
            <def>stubborn.</def>
         </entry>
         <ab type="heading"
             xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-d0e641"
             subtype="h1">Young / Old</ab>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-idp3257728">
            <form>
               <orth>pocan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>tubby, cheeky boy.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-idp3259240">
            <form>
               <orth>[ioncag]</orth>
            </form>
            <def>“Cha deach ioncag air.” – He has not grown an inch.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="AOHenley_ClarkstonRMacNeilnadur-idp3260824">
            <form>
               <orth>[stòlda]</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Bodach stòlda – for a child who talks like an adult. Cailleach stòlda – for a girl who talks like an adult.</def>
         </entry>
